Description: Chroma-only quantization tuning for the CLASSIC RemoteFX path
 (max_bpp=24). On that path xrdp calls rfxcodec_encode with quants=NULL, so
 librfxcodec used a single default quant vector for Y, Cb AND Cr — meaning you
 could not refine chroma without also spending bytes on luma.
 .
 This makes the default a TWO-set table: set [0] = luma (unchanged), set [1] =
 a finer chroma vector (tighter mid/high sub-bands). The classic tile loops are
 taught to point Cb/Cr at set [1] when the built-in default is in use (cidx),
 while callers that supply their own quants keep per-tile indexing (cidx = -1).
 Result: sharper colour / less hue around text with luma bandwidth untouched.
 .
 numQuants becomes 2 only for the default path; the extra 5-byte quant array is
 spec-legal (MS-RDPRFX allows multiple quant arrays + per-tile indices) and
 clients (mstsc/FreeRDP) decode it natively. The progressive region composer
 (rfx_compose_message_region) still sets num_quants=1 explicitly, so it reads
 only set [0] and is unaffected. Only the YUV tile loops are touched (xrdp
 encodes RFX_FORMAT_YUV); the RGB/ARGB loops are left as-is.
 .
 Sub-band order: LL3, LH3, HL3, HH3, LH2, HL2, HH2, LH1, HL1, HH1. Tunable:
 lower the set [1] nibbles for crisper chroma / more bytes.
 .
 Scope: bundled librfxcodec in the xrdp source; classic RFX only. The GFX
 Progressive path (max_bpp=32) is tuned in xrdp/xrdp_encoder.c
 (fleet-rfx-chroma-quant.patch).
Author: xrdp-fleet
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-06-14
